Citation.sTitle: Enthalpy of solution of CO2 in aqueous solutions of methyldiethanolamine at T = 372.9 K and pressures up to 5 MPa
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental enthalpies of solution of CO2 in aqueous solution of methyldiethanolamine (MDEA) of 15 wt% and 30 wt% are reported. The measurements were performed using a flow calorimetric technique at temperature of 372.9 K and pressures range from 0.5 MPa to 5 MPa. Gas solubilities data at same temperature and pressures were derived from the enthalpy data. Experimental enthalpies of solution are combined with available literature data in order to examine pressure and composition influences.
